resources.string: The Dassam Falls is 40 kilometres (25 mi) from Ranchi on NH 33 or Ranchi-Jamshedpur highway.
The Hundru Falls is a waterfall located in Ranchi district in the Indian state of Jharkhand. It is the 34th highest waterfall in India.
Sita falls is located in Ramgarh district of Jharkhand state. The district is located at 23°20’30″N 85°38’38″E.

Hirni Falls is a waterfall located in West Singhbhum in the Indian state of Jharkhand
The Pitthas in Jharkhand have a flavour of their own and is eaten with a variety of side dishes which sets it apart.
Dhuska is one of the most popular items in Jharkhand and is a part of every household. Your journey to Jharkhand is incomplete without tasting Dhuska
Rugra is an item which tastes like mushroom and is very delicious to eat. Rugra is basically an indigenous variety of vegetable, rich in protein and minerals and high on calorific value
It has been used as a sweet snack in the region since centuries and is considered a revered Prasad during the Chatth Pooja.
Litti is a very famous food item in the State and savoured by the locals. It is eaten with Yoghurt, Baigan Bharta (Chokha), Alu Bharta or Papad.
Chilka Roti is one of those dishes which are prepared using rice flour and besan.
The local people prepare a variety of dishes from the bamboo shot and mainly use it as a vegetable. You have to try it to experience its out-of-the-world flavour

Rock Garden in Ranchi is considered to be one of the most visited places of the city as well as the state.
The Tagore Hill also known as Morabadi Hill is situated in Morabadi, Ranchi, Jharkhand.It's a place of attraction for jharkhand tourism due to its connection with great poet Rabindra Nath Tagore.
